  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>grapes</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>freekeh</strong>, then add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 20-25 min or until tender but with a bite, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped grapes</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a baking tray (use<strong> tin foil </strong>to avoid mess!)</p><p>Drizzle <strong>half</strong> the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> over the <strong>grapes</strong> and drizzle the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> with<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Season both with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the broccoli has lightly charred</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to a separate baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the freekeh is cooking, combine the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar </strong>with half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining wholegrain mustard for another recipe!</p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>balsamic-mustard dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>roasted Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the pot with the<strong> drained freekeh</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and mix everything together</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> from the oven and chop it roughly with a sharp knife</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-grape-bacon-and-cracked-freekeh-bowl/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>broccoli & freekeh </strong>over the<strong> rocket</strong>, then top with the<strong> chopped bacon </strong>and <strong>roasted grapes</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>balsamic-mustard dressing</strong> all over and season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
